		"On-demand Component and API Auto-Importing": {
			"name": "On-demand Component and API Auto-Importing",
			"simSteps": [
				{
					"simStepId": "5f65bec1-2206-4255-83bb-917124fc48b5",
					"diagramNodeId": "ded5a514-3b2d-420d-b470-d672fd8dee15",
					"simStepLabel": "Flow 1: Configure Component Auto-Importing",
					"simStepDescription": "The Vite build process starts by reading `vite.config.ts`. The `unplugin-vue-components` plugin is configured to automatically discover and register Vue components from specified directories.",
					"isEdge": 0,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "vite.config.ts",
						"startLine": "68",
						"endLine": "75",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"Components"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"extensions\": [\"vue\", \"md\"],\n  \"include\": [\"/\\\\.vue$/\", \"/\\\\.vue\\\\?vue/\", \"/\\\\.md$/\"],\n  \"dts\": \"src/components.d.ts\"\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "25944f57-eabf-4ef1-baa0-61bd8cdea3ca",
					"diagramNodeId": "ab03d516-7b2e-4d83-a0de-5ddd7eb2f0ff",
					"simStepLabel": "Data Transformation: Plugin Scans Component Directories",
					"simStepDescription": "The `unplugin-vue-components` plugin scans the project for components based on its configuration. By default, it looks in `src/components` and finds files like `TheCounter.vue`, `TheFooter.vue`, and `TheInput.vue`.",
					"isEdge": 1,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "vite.config.ts",
						"startLine": "69",
						"endLine": "69",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"Components"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"scanDirectories\": [\"src/components\"],\n  \"fileExtensions\": [\"vue\", \"md\"]\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"scanDirectories\": [\"src/components\"],\n  \"fileExtensions\": [\"vue\", \"md\"]\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "9506f028-40e7-482b-9a4a-478e5ea6fcb6",
					"diagramNodeId": "b5aa4dce-0529-43c1-b827-c112e305055f",
					"simStepLabel": "Generate Component Type Definitions",
					"simStepDescription": "Based on the found components, the plugin generates the `src/components.d.ts` file. This file provides global TypeScript definitions for the components, allowing them to be used in templates without explicit imports and with full type support in the IDE.",
					"isEdge": 0,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "src/components.d.ts",
						"startLine": "8",
						"endLine": "17",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"GlobalComponents"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"foundComponents\": {\n    \"TheCounter\": \"./src/components/TheCounter.vue\",\n    \"TheFooter\": \"./src/components/TheFooter.vue\",\n    \"TheInput\": \"./src/components/TheInput.vue\"\n  }\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "/* eslint-disable */\n// @ts-nocheck\n// Generated by unplugin-vue-components\n// Read more: https://github.com/vuejs/core/pull/3399\nexport {}\n\n/* prettier-ignore */\ndeclare module 'vue' {\n  export interface GlobalComponents {\n    TheCounter: typeof import('./components/TheCounter.vue')['default']\n    TheFooter: typeof import('./components/TheFooter.vue')['default']\n    TheInput: typeof import('./components/TheInput.vue')['default']\n  }\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "1710b354-6f5e-4c21-808a-783dc3973913",
					"diagramNodeId": "eeb16291-a0ad-42e8-8cd1-d6f8c274b4a4",
					"simStepLabel": "Developer Uses Auto-Imported Component",
					"simStepDescription": "A developer can now use a component like `<TheFooter />` directly in any other component's template. The Vue Language Server (Volar) reads the generated `components.d.ts` to provide intellisense. The developer does not need to write an import statement.",
					"isEdge": 1,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "src/components.d.ts",
						"startLine": "14",
						"endLine": "14",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"TheFooter"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"template\": \"<template>\\n  <main>...</main>\\n  <TheFooter />\\n</template>\"\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"template\": \"<template>\\n  <main>...</main>\\n  <TheFooter />\\n</template>\"\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "0d7c181e-3eac-4805-9d19-c8d82dd0643a",
					"diagramNodeId": "356d8b73-9faf-4b31-a833-ccca46763127",
					"simStepLabel": "Build-Time Component Resolution",
					"simStepDescription": "During the Vite build process, the Vue template compiler encounters a tag like `<TheFooter />`. The `unplugin-vue-components` plugin intercepts this, resolves it to the actual file path, and effectively injects `import TheFooter from 'src/components/TheFooter.vue'` behind the scenes before the final code is bundled.",
					"isEdge": 0,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "vite.config.ts",
						"startLine": "68",
						"endLine": "75",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"Components"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"componentTag\": \"<TheFooter />\"\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"transformedCode\": \"import TheFooter from '/src/components/TheFooter.vue'; ... _createVNode(TheFooter)\"\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "477b57a4-0018-4b11-8fc5-061e8cf7ad15",
					"diagramNodeId": "8633f810-4638-407c-ba47-34542bbc5baf",
					"simStepLabel": "Flow 2: Configure API Auto-Importing",
					"simStepDescription": "In `vite.config.ts`, the `unplugin-auto-import` plugin is configured. It's set up to find and globally expose APIs (like `ref` or `computed`) from specified libraries (e.g., 'vue', '@vueuse/core') and custom directories ('src/composables').",
					"isEdge": 0,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "vite.config.ts",
						"startLine": "46",
						"endLine": "66",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"AutoImport"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"imports\": [\n    \"vue\",\n    \"vue-i18n\",\n    \"@vueuse/core\"\n  ],\n  \"dirs\": [\n    \"src/composables\",\n    \"src/stores\"\n  ],\n  \"dts\": \"src/auto-imports.d.ts\"\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "0c32a282-5635-4f34-bba2-3debb23a0142",
					"diagramNodeId": "85199f06-ba93-448b-a9c9-6ae9130ae1b7",
					"simStepLabel": "Data Transformation: Plugin Scans for APIs",
					"simStepDescription": "The plugin processes the `imports` presets (like 'vue') and scans the directories listed in `dirs` for exported functions and variables. For example, it finds `isDark` and `toggleDark` in `src/composables/dark.ts`.",
					"isEdge": 1,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "vite.config.ts",
						"startLine": "49",
						"endLine": "64",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"imports",
							"dirs"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"scanSources\": {\n    \"presets\": [\"vue\", \"vue-i18n\", \"@vueuse/core\"],\n    \"directories\": [\"src/composables\", \"src/stores\"]\n  }\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"scanSources\": {\n    \"presets\": [\"vue\", \"vue-i18n\", \"@vueuse/core\"],\n    \"directories\": [\"src/composables\", \"src/stores\"]\n  }\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "b04e9b59-4430-4671-b880-3e4a68a6b4cc",
					"diagramNodeId": "57a71840-22ad-4e04-a292-3edc6824342c",
					"simStepLabel": "Generate API Type Definitions",
					"simStepDescription": "The plugin generates `src/auto-imports.d.ts`, which declares all discovered APIs (e.g., `ref`, `computed`, `useHead`, `useI18n`, `isDark`) as global constants. This provides TypeScript with the necessary type information, enabling autocompletion and preventing 'not defined' errors in the IDE.",
					"isEdge": 0,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "src/auto-imports.d.ts",
						"startLine": "8",
						"endLine": "9",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"declare global"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"foundAPIs\": [\"ref\", \"computed\", \"useI18n\", \"isDark\", \"useHead\"]\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "declare global {\n  const ref: typeof import('vue')['ref']\n  const useI18n: typeof import('vue-i18n')['useI18n']\n  const isDark: typeof import('./composables/dark')['isDark']\n  const useHead: typeof import('@unhead/vue')['useHead']\n  // ... and many more\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "cc6312ab-3e2a-4840-9b66-4791f616b6f5",
					"diagramNodeId": "194e9d34-fe71-451f-a09c-3a829448ae7f",
					"simStepLabel": "Developer Uses Auto-Imported API",
					"simStepDescription": "A developer can now call a globally available function like `useI18n()` directly within a `<script>` block, as seen in `src/pages/about.md`, without an explicit import statement.",
					"isEdge": 1,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "src/pages/about.md",
						"startLine": "6",
						"endLine": "6",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"useI18n"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"code\": \"const { t } = useI18n()\"\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"code\": \"const { t } = useI18n()\"\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "46ecbd64-0ee2-4bee-a3a1-bebfce34f25d",
					"diagramNodeId": "6c26b624-d46c-4d74-b3c9-6df238bc9f0c",
					"simStepLabel": "Build-Time Code Transformation",
					"simStepDescription": "When Vite processes a file, the `unplugin-auto-import` plugin scans the code for usage of these global APIs. Upon finding `useI18n`, it transparently injects the necessary `import { useI18n } from 'vue-i18n'` statement at the top of the script. This transformed code is then passed to the rest of the build chain.",
					"isEdge": 0,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "vite.config.ts",
						"startLine": "46",
						"endLine": "66",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"AutoImport"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"originalCode\": \"<script setup>\\nconst { t } = useI18n()\\n</script>\"\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"transformedCode\": \"import { useI18n } from 'vue-i18n';\\n<script setup>\\nconst { t } = useI18n()\\n</script>\"\n}"
				}
			],
			"description": "<ul><li>This feature drastically reduces boilerplate by automatically importing components and common APIs</li><li>- Vue components placed in <code>src/components</code> are automatically registered and can be used in templates without any import statements</li><li>- Core Vue Composition APIs (<code>ref</code>, <code>computed</code>, etc</li><li>), VueUse functions, and custom composables from <code>src/composables</code> are globally available in scripts</li><li>- This leads to cleaner, more readable code and significantly faster development, configured via plugins in <code>vite</li><li>config</li><li>ts</code></li></ul>",
			"simulationNodesAndEdges": {
				"ded5a514-3b2d-420d-b470-d672fd8dee15": {
