		"Integrated State Management with Pinia": {
			"name": "Integrated State Management with Pinia",
			"simSteps": [
				{
					"simStepId": "06968957-b1c7-4a4e-a473-b40c12f0af9a",
					"diagramNodeId": "469298e3-fcfe-447a-8cb6-03d2e8a1fd4f",
					"simStepLabel": "Pinia: Initialize Pinia Instance",
					"simStepDescription": "The application setup process invokes the `install` function, which is a ViteSSG UserModule. Inside this function, a new Pinia instance is created using `createPinia()`.",
					"isEdge": 0,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "src/modules/pinia.ts",
						"startLine": "6",
						"endLine": "8",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"install",
							"createPinia",
							"pinia",
							"app"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"isClient\": false,\n  \"initialState\": {},\n  \"app\": \"<Vue App instance>\"\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"pinia\": \"<Pinia instance>\"\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "abd08389-af54-4278-ab84-f8dd84ae3df4",
					"diagramNodeId": "e40fbac0-26fe-4723-81a1-33e6b7aaaf3f",
					"simStepLabel": "Pinia: Register with Vue App",
					"simStepDescription": "The newly created Pinia instance is registered as a plugin with the main Vue application instance via `app.use(pinia)`. This makes Pinia's state management capabilities available throughout the entire component tree.",
					"isEdge": 1,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "src/modules/pinia.ts",
						"startLine": "8",
						"endLine": "8",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"app.use"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"pinia\": \"<Pinia instance>\"\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"pinia\": \"<Pinia instance>\"\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "036d855a-51ff-4940-943b-23bc4f677d1c",
					"diagramNodeId": "fe5e70c8-fc2f-48b1-af40-df874a8ad225",
					"simStepLabel": "Pinia: Server-Side State Serialization",
					"simStepDescription": "During Server-Side Generation (SSG), where `isClient` is false, the application's current state is captured from the Pinia instance (`pinia.state.value`) and stored in the `initialState.pinia` object. This object will be serialized by ViteSSG.",
					"isEdge": 0,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "src/modules/pinia.ts",
						"startLine": "15",
						"endLine": "16",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"initialState",
							"pinia.state.value"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"isClient\": false,\n  \"initialState\": {},\n  \"pinia.state.value\": {\n    \"user\": {\n      \"savedName\": \"John\",\n      \"previousNames\": []\n    }\n  }\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"initialState\": {\n    \"pinia\": {\n      \"user\": {\n        \"savedName\": \"John\",\n        \"previousNames\": []\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "1b5ac957-6ec8-45d5-af32-1e3db57424db",
					"diagramNodeId": "1f7264f9-fdb2-458d-a6e6-50aeb5ffc0a3",
					"simStepLabel": "Pinia: Transmit Initial State to Client",
					"simStepDescription": "ViteSSG serializes the `initialState` object, including the captured Pinia state, and embeds it into the initial HTML document that is sent to the browser. This ensures the client starts with the same state as the server.",
					"isEdge": 1,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "src/modules/pinia.ts",
						"startLine": "10",
						"endLine": "10",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"// https://github.com/antfu/vite-ssg/blob/main/README.md#state-serialization"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"initialState\": {\n    \"pinia\": {\n      \"user\": {\n        \"savedName\": \"John\",\n        \"previousNames\": []\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"initialState\": {\n    \"pinia\": {\n      \"user\": {\n        \"savedName\": \"John\",\n        \"previousNames\": []\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "d34c4c82-4aa8-4cf0-9653-c2ed5f8b4fee",
					"diagramNodeId": "d62ac2e6-386c-449b-b029-6d3f4cc4ca98",
					"simStepLabel": "Pinia: Client-Side State Hydration",
					"simStepDescription": "When the application boots up in the browser, the `install` function runs again. This time `isClient` is true, and the logic hydrates the new client-side Pinia instance with the state received from the server via `initialState.pinia`.",
					"isEdge": 0,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "src/modules/pinia.ts",
						"startLine": "12",
						"endLine": "13",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"isClient",
							"pinia.state.value",
							"initialState.pinia"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"isClient\": true,\n  \"initialState\": {\n    \"pinia\": {\n      \"user\": {\n        \"savedName\": \"John\",\n        \"previousNames\": []\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"pinia.state.value\": {\n    \"user\": {\n      \"savedName\": \"John\",\n      \"previousNames\": []\n    }\n  }\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "195c50d2-7e98-4879-87a8-cb05cc474e72",
					"diagramNodeId": "c1ba3f9d-1122-4bf7-9a6b-f82911850216",
					"simStepLabel": "Pinia: Define User Store",
					"simStepDescription": "The user store is defined in `src/stores/user.ts` using `defineStore`. This function sets up the store's ID ('user'), state (`savedName`, `previousNames`), computed properties (`otherNames`), and actions (`setNewName`). It returns the `useUserStore` composable function.",
					"isEdge": 0,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "src/stores/user.ts",
						"startLine": "3",
						"endLine": "31",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"defineStore",
							"useUserStore",
							"savedName",
							"previousNames",
							"setNewName"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"id\": \"user\",\n  \"setup\": \"() => { ... }\"\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"useUserStore\": \"<Composable function>\"\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "723122d7-3c1b-477d-9d86-0d01e7ee8d90",
					"diagramNodeId": "a73d378c-9581-4aa3-88d4-a352b96fdcad",
					"simStepLabel": "Vite: Configure Store Auto-Import",
					"simStepDescription": "The `unplugin-auto-import` plugin is configured in `vite.config.ts`. It's instructed to scan the `src/stores` directory to make any exported composables, like `useUserStore`, globally available without needing explicit import statements in components.",
					"isEdge": 1,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "vite.config.ts",
						"startLine": "61",
						"endLine": "64",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"AutoImport",
							"dirs"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"pluginConfig\": {\n    \"dirs\": [\n      \"src/composables\",\n      \"src/stores\"\n    ]\n  }\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"pluginConfig\": {\n    \"dirs\": [\n      \"src/composables\",\n      \"src/stores\"\n    ]\n  }\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "a89c872b-1ec6-4506-8b32-17ff61f32ab1",
					"diagramNodeId": "0c5faa3c-a18d-449f-a862-870f368013f6",
					"simStepLabel": "Vite: Generate Auto-Import Declarations",
					"simStepDescription": "Based on the configuration, `unplugin-auto-import` generates a TypeScript declaration file (`src/auto-imports.d.ts`) that globally declares `useUserStore`, providing type safety and editor autocompletion across the project.",
					"isEdge": 0,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "src/auto-imports.d.ts",
						"startLine": "282",
						"endLine": "282",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"useUserStore"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"stores\": {\n    \"user\": \"export const useUserStore = ...\"\n  }\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"declaration\": \"const useUserStore: typeof import('./stores/user')['useUserStore']\"\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "d1e48020-e143-4942-8e22-fc990f97de17",
					"diagramNodeId": "5c166ef4-8896-4cc9-b20f-b1bee4bfa1b2",
					"simStepLabel": "Component: Access the Store",
					"simStepDescription": "In a component, such as `/hi/[name].vue`, the globally available `useUserStore()` composable is called to get access to the user store instance. This instance is reactive and can be used to read state or call actions.",
					"isEdge": 0,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "src/pages/hi/[name].vue",
						"startLine": "4",
						"endLine": "4",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"user",
							"useUserStore"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"user\": {\n    \"savedName\": \"John\",\n    \"otherNames\": [],\n    \"setNewName\": \"<function>\"\n  }\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "e21172fc-e924-465e-93bb-129299e04046",
					"diagramNodeId": "bd83f504-46fb-47a3-97ac-8c839fd96627",
					"simStepLabel": "Data Flow: Pass Route Parameter to Action",
					"simStepDescription": "The component uses a `watchEffect` to react to changes in the route. It retrieves the `name` parameter from `route.params` and passes it as an argument to the `user.setNewName` action.",
					"isEdge": 1,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "src/pages/hi/[name].vue",
						"startLine": "7",
						"endLine": "9",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"watchEffect",
							"user.setNewName",
							"route.params.name"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"route.params.name\": \"Vitesse\"\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"route.params.name\": \"Vitesse\"\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "8e7df95a-50af-4843-8f59-c05a12e2405c",
					"diagramNodeId": "ed42ea0c-c7f4-46b6-bbf5-e7f5210ad5b2",
					"simStepLabel": "Pinia: Update State via Action",
					"simStepDescription": "The `setNewName` action within the user store is executed. It updates the `savedName` ref with the new name and adds the previous name to the `previousNames` set, demonstrating state mutation within a Pinia action.",
					"isEdge": 0,
