		"Static Site Generation (SSG) for Performance and SEO": {
			"name": "Static Site Generation (SSG) for Performance and SEO",
			"simSteps": [
				{
					"simStepId": "55371288-f6df-481f-a218-ddc7aed45773",
					"diagramNodeId": "b3b4ee60-e621-41d8-9708-7f0bd05da5ca",
					"simStepLabel": "Build: Load Vite Configuration",
					"simStepDescription": "The `pnpm build` command initiates the Vite build process. Vite loads `vite.config.ts`, which contains the configuration for Static Site Generation (SSG) via `vite-ssg`. The `ssgOptions` object defines how SSG will be performed, including script loading, formatting, critical CSS options, and a post-generation hook.",
					"isEdge": 0,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "vite.config.ts",
						"startLine": "152",
						"endLine": "161",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"ssgOptions",
							"beastiesOptions",
							"onFinished"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"command\": \"pnpm build\"\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"ssgOptions\": {\n    \"script\": \"async\",\n    \"formatting\": \"minify\",\n    \"beastiesOptions\": {\n      \"reduceInlineStyles\": false\n    },\n    \"onFinished\": \"function() { generateSitemap() }\"\n  }\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "0d79dd5e-e654-43e6-9d82-69a4254aa8f8",
					"diagramNodeId": "4ae95f08-3ff7-4e41-a563-782fb63dcc6d",
					"simStepLabel": "Build: Pass Config to vite-ssg",
					"simStepDescription": "The loaded configuration, particularly `ssgOptions`, is passed to the `vite-ssg` engine, which takes control of the build process to perform static site generation instead of a standard client-side build.",
					"isEdge": 1,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "vite.config.ts",
						"startLine": "152",
						"endLine": "161",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"ssgOptions"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"ssgOptions\": {\n    \"script\": \"async\",\n    \"formatting\": \"minify\",\n    \"beastiesOptions\": {\n      \"reduceInlineStyles\": false\n    },\n    \"onFinished\": \"function() { generateSitemap() }\"\n  }\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"ssgOptions\": {\n    \"script\": \"async\",\n    \"formatting\": \"minify\",\n    \"beastiesOptions\": {\n      \"reduceInlineStyles\": false\n    },\n    \"onFinished\": \"function() { generateSitemap() }\"\n  }\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "30e81ffb-c3d9-4814-8ff3-e4820cab536f",
					"diagramNodeId": "5bf97fa8-8d70-4955-b5f9-0bbc76f5c531",
					"simStepLabel": "Build: Initialize Vue App with ViteSSG",
					"simStepDescription": "The `vite-ssg` process finds and executes the `createApp` export from the entry point `src/main.ts`. This function configures `ViteSSG` with the root Vue component (`App.vue`), the application routes, and a callback function to install modules like Pinia and Vue I18n on the app instance.",
					"isEdge": 0,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "src/main.ts",
						"startLine": "13",
						"endLine": "17",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"createApp",
							"ViteSSG",
							"App",
							"routes",
							"setupLayouts"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"App\": \"<VueComponent>\",\n  \"options\": {\n    \"routes\": [\n      {\n        \"path\": \"/\",\n        \"component\": \".../pages/index.vue\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"path\": \"/about\",\n        \"component\": \".../pages/about.md\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"createApp\": \"<Function>\"\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "ecd4cad6-189b-415a-bedf-5aaae8cf0641",
					"diagramNodeId": "21d4ce6f-5edb-46c0-bdf2-289c61e2dfe5",
					"simStepLabel": "Build: Pass SSG Context to Modules",
					"simStepDescription": "For each page to be rendered, `vite-ssg` creates a context object containing the app instance, router, an `initialState` object for serialization, and a flag `isClient` (which is `false` during SSG). This context is then passed to each user module's `install` function.",
					"isEdge": 1,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "src/main.ts",
						"startLine": "21",
						"endLine": "22",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"ctx"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"ctx\": {\n    \"app\": \"<VueAppInstance>\",\n    \"router\": \"<VueRouterInstance>\",\n    \"routes\": \"<RouteRecordRaw[]>\",\n    \"isClient\": false,\n    \"initialState\": {},\n    \"head\": \"<UnheadInstance>\"\n  }\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"ctx\": {\n    \"app\": \"<VueAppInstance>\",\n    \"router\": \"<VueRouterInstance>\",\n    \"routes\": \"<RouteRecordRaw[]>\",\n    \"isClient\": false,\n    \"initialState\": {},\n    \"head\": \"<UnheadInstance>\"\n  }\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "08e11117-a6a4-463e-ac9c-fc955f2aaa9b",
					"diagramNodeId": "446b66f9-c54e-43ee-a14c-e64578aa9043",
					"simStepLabel": "Build: Populate Initial State via Pinia Module",
					"simStepDescription": "The Pinia module (`src/modules/pinia.ts`) is executed. Since `isClient` is false, it populates `initialState.pinia` with the current state of all Pinia stores. This state will be serialized and embedded into the generated HTML to be hydrated on the client-side.",
					"isEdge": 0,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "src/modules/pinia.ts",
						"startLine": "6",
						"endLine": "17",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"install",
							"isClient",
							"initialState",
							"pinia"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"ctx\": {\n    \"isClient\": false,\n    \"initialState\": {},\n    \"app\": \"<VueAppInstance>\"\n  }\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"initialState\": {\n    \"pinia\": {\n      \"user\": {\n        \"name\": \"\",\n        \"otherNames\": []\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "b17ad843-f459-4b06-bb0f-a93d9fff04f1",
					"diagramNodeId": "c3c05b32-e546-4b0e-9ffe-a9d87220ca15",
					"simStepLabel": "Build: Page Data to Renderer",
					"simStepDescription": "After all modules run, `vite-ssg` takes the fully configured app instance for a specific route, along with the populated initial state and head metadata, and sends it to the rendering engine.",
					"isEdge": 1,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "src/App.vue",
						"startLine": "5",
						"endLine": "8",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"useHead"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"route\": \"/\",\n  \"app\": \"<ConfiguredVueApp>\",\n  \"head\": {\n    \"title\": \"Vitesse\",\n    \"meta\": [\n      {\n        \"name\": \"description\",\n        \"content\": \"Opinionated Vite Starter Template\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"route\": \"/\",\n  \"app\": \"<ConfiguredVueApp>\",\n  \"head\": {\n    \"title\": \"Vitesse\",\n    \"meta\": [\n      {\n        \"name\": \"description\",\n        \"content\": \"Opinionated Vite Starter Template\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "41d3b6c4-93c7-495d-a2d8-aa844922bb3a",
					"diagramNodeId": "eb406743-fc1d-4133-86a3-534cb6e512e5",
					"simStepLabel": "Build: Inline Critical CSS",
					"simStepDescription": "For each rendered page, `vite-ssg` uses the 'beasties' tool to identify the CSS rules necessary for the initial viewport (critical CSS). These styles are then inlined into a `<style>` tag in the `<head>` of the final HTML document, ensuring the page renders content as quickly as possible without waiting for external stylesheets.",
					"isEdge": 0,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "vite.config.ts",
						"startLine": "155",
						"endLine": "157",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"beastiesOptions"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"html\": \"<html>...<link rel='stylesheet' href='style.css'>...</html>\",\n  \"beastiesOptions\": {\n    \"reduceInlineStyles\": false\n  }\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"html\": \"<html><head><style>/* critical styles */</style></head>...</html>\"\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "a8b12c4b-3541-4383-825d-57bd86b876ee",
					"diagramNodeId": "28d09a65-62c8-4936-8545-55ffc7c56348",
					"simStepLabel": "Build: Completion Signal to `onFinished` Hook",
					"simStepDescription": "After all pages are rendered, critical CSS is inlined, and files are written to the `dist` directory, the `vite-ssg` process emits a completion signal that triggers the `onFinished` hook defined in the configuration.",
					"isEdge": 1,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "vite.config.ts",
						"startLine": "158",
						"endLine": "158",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"onFinished"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"outputDir\": \"dist\"\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"outputDir\": \"dist\"\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "4c6e794a-ff9f-4e39-80d6-11684d8190eb",
					"diagramNodeId": "a4509451-8f0f-4e67-a894-400f99ee7830",
					"simStepLabel": "Build: Generate Sitemap",
					"simStepDescription": "The `onFinished` hook calls `generateSitemap()`. This function, provided by `vite-ssg-sitemap`, inspects the generated static files in the `dist` directory and creates a `sitemap.xml` file. This file lists all available pages, which helps search engines discover and index the site's content more effectively.",
					"isEdge": 0,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "vite.config.ts",
						"startLine": "158",
						"endLine": "160",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"onFinished",
							"generateSitemap"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"hostname\": \"https://example.com/\",\n  \"routes\": [\n    \"/\",\n    \"/about\",\n    \"/hi/john\"\n  ]\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"filePath\": \"dist/sitemap.xml\",\n  \"content\": \"<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?><urlset><url><loc>https://example.com/</loc></url><url><loc>https://example.com/about</loc></url></urlset>\"\n}"
				}
			],
			"description": "<ul><li>The project is configured for Static Site Generation (SSG), which pre-renders pages into static HTML at build time</li><li>- This results in extremely fast load times, improved reliability, and excellent SEO</li><li>- It uses <code>vite-ssg</code> which also handles critical CSS inlining and automatic sitemap generation</li><li>- Running <code>pnpm build</code> creates a production-ready <code>dist</code> folder that can be deployed to any static host</li></ul>",
			"simulationNodesAndEdges": {
