			"simSteps": [],
			"description": "<ul><li>Developers can use Markdown for content-rich pages or components seamlessly</li><li>- <code></li><li>md</code> files in the <code>src/pages</code> directory are automatically converted into application routes</li><li>- It supports embedding interactive Vue components directly inside Markdown files</li><li>- Server-side syntax highlighting for code blocks is included via Shiki, as demonstrated in <code>src/pages/about</li><li>md</code></li></ul>",
