		"Progressive Web App (PWA) Readiness": {
			"name": "Progressive Web App (PWA) Readiness",
			"simSteps": [
				{
					"simStepId": "8977113e-252f-41ca-a0c1-6cbd00a12d9f",
					"diagramNodeId": "4547ad22-1b50-4478-be42-339d282f3431",
					"simStepLabel": "PWA Plugin Configuration",
					"simStepDescription": "The vite-plugin-pwa is configured in the main Vite configuration file. This setup defines the behavior of the Progressive Web App, including setting the service worker update strategy to 'autoUpdate' and specifying the contents of the web app manifest, such as the app's name, theme color, and icons.",
					"isEdge": 0,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "vite.config.ts",
						"startLine": "105",
						"endLine": "118",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"VitePWA"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"registerType\": \"autoUpdate\",\n  \"includeAssets\": [\"favicon.svg\", \"safari-pinned-tab.svg\"],\n  \"manifest\": {\n    \"name\": \"Vitesse\",\n    \"short_name\": \"Vitesse\",\n    \"theme_color\": \"#ffffff\",\n    \"icons\": [\n      {\n        \"src\": \"/pwa-192x192.png\",\n        \"sizes\": \"192x192\",\n        \"type\": \"image/png\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"pluginName\": \"vite-plugin-pwa\",\n  \"status\": \"configured\"\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "1584339b-7cef-4838-b075-90cda6bc2aab",
					"diagramNodeId": "5ae064ac-7109-463d-9708-b17864c3f459",
					"simStepLabel": "Build Process Generation",
					"simStepDescription": "During the build process, Vite and the PWA plugin use the configuration to automatically generate the necessary PWA assets. This includes creating the `manifest.webmanifest` file, generating the service worker script (e.g., `sw.js`), and injecting the manifest link into the final `index.html` in the `dist` directory.",
					"isEdge": 1,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "vite.config.ts",
						"startLine": "105",
						"endLine": "118",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"VitePWA"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"registerType\": \"autoUpdate\",\n  \"manifest\": {\n    \"name\": \"Vitesse\",\n    \"icons\": [\n      {\n        \"src\": \"/pwa-192x192.png\",\n        \"sizes\": \"192x192\",\n        \"type\": \"image/png\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"registerType\": \"autoUpdate\",\n  \"manifest\": {\n    \"name\": \"Vitesse\",\n    \"icons\": [\n      {\n        \"src\": \"/pwa-192x192.png\",\n        \"sizes\": \"192x192\",\n        \"type\": \"image/png\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "a21a1239-fa21-4117-b434-f5952242f9f5",
					"diagramNodeId": "a1535fae-0236-4b23-869b-6cea75e98881",
					"simStepLabel": "App Initialization and Module Loading",
					"simStepDescription": "The application's entry point, `main.ts`, uses ViteSSG to create the Vue app. It then dynamically imports all files from the `./modules` directory and executes their `install` function, passing in the application context. This modular approach ensures the PWA registration logic is automatically included.",
					"isEdge": 0,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "src/main.ts",
						"startLine": "21",
						"endLine": "22",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"import.meta.glob",
							"i.install"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"ctx\": {\n    \"app\": \"<Vue App Instance>\",\n    \"router\": \"<Vue Router Instance>\",\n    \"isClient\": true,\n    \"initialState\": {}\n  }\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "3ca07b8f-5a18-4cff-92b2-fa5f17fce4f4",
					"diagramNodeId": "f77ca2b5-b61c-4444-8bb2-86b29768bba5",
					"simStepLabel": "Pass Context to PWA Module",
					"simStepDescription": "The application context, which includes the app instance, router, and client-side status, is passed from `main.ts` to the `install` function within the `src/modules/pwa.ts` module.",
					"isEdge": 1,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "src/main.ts",
						"startLine": "22",
						"endLine": "22",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"i.install",
							"ctx"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"ctx\": {\n    \"app\": \"<Vue App Instance>\",\n    \"router\": \"<Vue Router Instance>\",\n    \"isClient\": true,\n    \"initialState\": {}\n  }\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"ctx\": {\n    \"app\": \"<Vue App Instance>\",\n    \"router\": \"<Vue Router Instance>\",\n    \"isClient\": true,\n    \"initialState\": {}\n  }\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "890ede66-7b9f-4956-bbba-10aba552f6da",
					"diagramNodeId": "870c2550-81b8-4aad-b30a-77cbb2f30db1",
					"simStepLabel": "Service Worker Registration",
					"simStepDescription": "The `install` function in the PWA module checks if it's running on the client. If so, it waits for the Vue router to be ready, then dynamically imports the `registerSW` function from a virtual module provided by `vite-plugin-pwa`. It immediately calls this function to register the service worker in the browser, enabling offline capabilities and auto-updates.",
					"isEdge": 0,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "src/modules/pwa.ts",
						"startLine": "4",
						"endLine": "7",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"install",
							"isClient",
							"router.isReady",
							"registerSW"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"ctx\": {\n    \"isClient\": true,\n    \"router\": \"<Vue Router Instance>\"\n  }\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"registrationOptions\": {\n    \"immediate\": true\n  }\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "75a6bd2d-239b-44d6-86fa-07cf658bd0a6",
					"diagramNodeId": "47dbb9d7-eaba-443d-801c-0c5ad54c8138",
					"simStepLabel": "Browser Service Worker API Call",
					"simStepDescription": "The `registerSW` function, provided by the 'virtual:pwa-register' module, internally uses the browser's native `navigator.serviceWorker.register()` API to install and activate the service worker script that was generated during the build process.",
					"isEdge": 1,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "src/modules/pwa.ts",
						"startLine": "11",
						"endLine": "11",
						"relevantVariables": [
							"registerSW"
						]
					},
					"inputDataExample": "{\n  \"registrationOptions\": {\n    \"immediate\": true\n  }\n}",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"registrationOptions\": {\n    \"immediate\": true\n  }\n}"
				},
				{
					"simStepId": "53cb79e9-52fb-4dd0-9325-838ad08d830b",
					"diagramNodeId": "4ef967ed-f9f0-4597-a050-2be5b4ab6928",
					"simStepLabel": "HTML Icon and Manifest Linkage",
					"simStepDescription": "The main `index.html` file includes a link to the `pwa-192x192.png` icon for `apple-touch-icon` compatibility. During the build, `vite-plugin-pwa` also injects a `<link rel=\"manifest\" href=\"/manifest.webmanifest\">` tag into the HTML head, allowing the browser to discover the web app's manifest file.",
					"isEdge": 0,
					"sourceCodeMapping": {
						"filePath": "index.html",
						"startLine": "6",
						"endLine": "6",
						"relevantVariables": []
					},
					"inputDataExample": "null",
					"outputDataExample": "{\n  \"htmlHeadLinks\": [\n    \"<link rel=\\\"apple-touch-icon\\\" href=\\\"/pwa-192x192.png\\\" />\",\n    \"<link rel=\\\"manifest\\\" href=\\\"/manifest.webmanifest\\\">\"\n  ]\n}"
				}
			],
			"description": "<ul><li>The template includes a PWA plugin to easily add app-like capabilities</li><li>- It automatically generates a web app manifest and a service worker for offline support</li><li>- This allows the application to be installable on a user's home screen</li><li>- The configuration in <code>vite</li><li>config</li><li>ts</code> is set to auto-update the PWA when new versions are deployed</li></ul>",
			"simulationNodesAndEdges": {
				"4547ad22-1b50-4478-be42-339d282f3431": {
					"simStepIds": [
						"8977113e-252f-41ca-a0c1-6cbd00a12d9f"
